# Overview
- This project is a monorepo landing page and dapp for Corbind
- It works with another repo only for smart contracts
- The journey (UX/UI) MUST remove objections

# Pages

## Landing page (/)
- Home: a SPA to show who is Corbind and invite leads to enter in the ecosystem

## DApp (/app)
- Home: CTAs in top, to invite writers to publish and readers to read a top pick book. Filters by category or text. Follow by a banner to show campaigns and other informations (e.g. book promotions) and then a list of carousel, each one is a category of books.
- Bookcase: a profile page to show all avaliable books (reading), want to read (watchlist) and favorite books.
- Publish: a place to up a epub or pdf, define title and other infos, then Corbind will publish it onchain and show in marketplace to read. The publish isn't a simple push to a store and download. See how publish works and how to recovery in @publish-read-workflow.mdc
- Book: a page to show details of the book with some actions (e.g. rent, save or share)
- ereader: a page to decrypt book content and show on screen (cannot copy content) if user pay for rent by 30 days 

# Stack

## Frontend
- Using NextJS, version 16 with ReactJS, version 19, to build the web app
- Use React Context to manage states
- Use Next Intl (i18n) to internationalization (en, pt-BR)
- Use Tailwind CSS to style
- Use Yup and Zod to forms
- Use Mui/icons-material and Mui/material to icons, svg and others
- Use privy as wallet connection (web3 plug-in-play)

## Code
- Should be responsible, thinking in mobile-first
- Use FSD Architecture to organize the code
- Prefer Component Composition 
- Prefer SSR instead
- Use Cache to increase perfomance
- Prefer divide UI/UX from business rules, using techniques like Pattern Container/Presentational.

